<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-15710] OpenTracingTracer does not activate created span</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-15710</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;OpenTracingTracer&lt;/tt&gt; does not activate the span it creates in &lt;tt&gt;onExchangeBegin&lt;/tt&gt; (i.e. does not invoke &lt;tt&gt;tracer.activateSpan&lt;/tt&gt;). Whenever there is processor invoked down the route, and this processor code is instrumented for OpenTracing (for instance, JDBC calls via &lt;tt&gt;opentracing-contrib/java-spring-cloud&lt;/tt&gt;), the newly created spans are not aware about a trace being active and start a new trace. This leads to all such spans being detached from the route trace. It is a major issue for Camel routes observability via OpenTracing.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
